JOHANNESBURG – The sentencing of Vicki Momberg, whose racist tirade was caught on camera, will be handed down next week. She appeared in the Randburg Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday morning where the matter was postponed to 28 March. [FULL REPORT] eNCA's @KhayaJames provides the latest on convicted racist, #VickyMomberg. Courtesy #DStv403 https://t.co/cmD5BJ8oxg She was convicted of crimen injuria because of her rant, which went viral on social media in early 2017. READ: Vicki Momberg breaks down in court Momberg was captured on camera, verbally abusing officers who had arrived to help her, following a smash-and-grab incident in Johannesburg. She repeatedly used the K-word and refused assistance from black officers, citing incompetence. eNCA